obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (39386)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39386&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Haryana and Uttar Pradesh (Alteration of Boundaries)`
  line `Act, 1979.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (39387)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39387&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed" day means the day which the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint;`
  line
  line `(b) “assembly constituency”, “council constituency” and “parliamentary constituency” have the`
  line `same meanings as in the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(c) "fixed boundaries" means the boundaries demarcated under the provisions of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "law" includes any enactment, Ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law, rule, scheme,`
  line `notification or other instrument having the force of law in the whole or in any part of the State of`
  line `Haryana or Uttar Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(e) "notified order" means an order published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "present deep stream line" means the deep stream line of the river-Yamuna as verified and`
  line `determined by the Survey of India during the months of November, 1974, December, 1974, January,`
  line `1975 and February, 1975;`
  line
  line `(h) "sitting member", in relation to either House of Parliament or of the Legislature of a State,`
  line `means a person who immediately before the appointed day is a member of that House;`
  line
  line `(i) "transferred territories" means,—`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to the State of Haryana, the territories transferred by this Act from that State to`
  line `the State of Uttar Pradesh, and`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to the State of Uttar Pradesh, the territories transferred by this Act from that`
  line `State to the State of Haryana;`
  line
  line `(j) any reference to a district of a State shall be construed as a reference to the area physically`
  line `comprised within that district immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (39388)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Replacement of fluctuating boundaries by fixed boundaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39388&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day,`
  line `the boundary between the Karnal and Sonepat districts of the State of Haryana and the Saharanpur,`
  line `Muzaffarnagar and Meerut districts of the State of Uttar Pradesh and the boundary between the Gurgaon`
  line `district of the State of Haryana and the Bulandshahr and Aligarh districts of the State of Uttar Pradesh`
  line `which at present is the deep stream of the river-Yamuna, shall be altered to and replaced by fixed`
  line boundaries.
  line
  line `(2) The said fixed boundaries shall be demarcated by an authority appointed in this behalf by the`
  line `Central Government so as to be generally in conformity with the fixed boundaries described in the`
  line Schedule.
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of such demarcation,—`
  line
  line `(a) the decision of the said authority on any matter relating to the interpretation of any part of the`
  line `description of the fixed boundary given in the Schedule shall be final;`
  line
  line `(b) the said authority shall have power to determine the location of the points at which the`
  line `boundary pillars shall be constructed and to specify the State Government which shall be responsible`
  line `for the construction and maintenance of the boundary pillars at such points according to such`
  line `specifications as that authority may indicate (the pillars of the same specifications being apportioned,`
  line `as far as practicable, equally between the two State Governments), the decision of the said authority`
  line `in regard to these matters being final;`
  line
  line `(c) it shall be lawful for the said authority and for any person specified by such authority to enter`
  line `upon and survey any area in the vicinity of any of the fixed boundaries described in the Schedule and`
  line `to do all other acts as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The authority referred to in sub-section (2) shall also prepare maps of the areas on both sides of`
  line `the fixed boundaries and in the vicinity thereof showing—`
  line
  line `(a) the present deep stream line and the fixed boundary in relation to it; and`
  line
  line `(b) the names and boundaries of the villages on both sides of the fixed boundary as indicated by`
  line `the State Government concerned with reference to the revenue records of that Government,`
  line
  line `and send authenticated copies thereof to the Central Government and to the State Governments of`
  line `Haryana and Uttar Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (39389)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Transfer of territories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39389&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be added to the State of Haryana all the territories of the State of Uttar Pradesh`
  line `which lie on the Haryana side of the fixed boundaries, and the said territories shall thereupon cease to`
  line `form part of the State of Uttar Pradesh; and`
  line
  line `(b) there shall be added to the State of Uttar Pradesh all the territories of the State of Haryana`
  line `which lie on the Uttar Pradesh side of the fixed boundaries, and the said territories shall thereupon`
  line `cease to form part of the State of Haryana.`
  line
  line `(2) Each of the State Governments of Haryana and Uttar Pradesh shall, by order in the Official`
  line `Gazette of the State, provide for the administration, as from the appointed day, of the territories`
  line `transferred to that State under sub-section (1) by including them or any part of them in such district,`
  line `sub-division, police-station or other administrative unit as may be specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (39390)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Amendment of First Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39390&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, in the First`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution, under the heading "I. THE STATES"—`
  line
  line `(a) for the entry against "13. Uttar Pradesh", the following shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"The territories which immediately before the commencement of this Constitution`
  line `were either comprised in the Province known as the United Provinces or were being administered`
  line `as if they formed part of that Province, the territories specified in clause (b) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 3 of the Bihar and Uttar Pradesh (Alteration of Boundaries) Act, 1968 (24 of 1968) and`
  line `the territories specified in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 4 of the Haryana and Uttar`
  line `Pradesh (Alteration of Boundaries) Act, 1979, but excluding the territories specified in clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Bihar and Uttar Pradesh (Alteration of Boundaries)`
  line `Act, 1968, and the territories specified in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 4 of the Haryana`
  line `and Uttar Pradesh (Alteration of Boundaries) Act, 1979 (31 of 1979).";`
  line
  line `(b) for the entry against "17. Haryana", the following shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"The territories specified in sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Punjab Reorganisation Act,`
  line `1966 and the territories specified in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 4 of the Haryana and`
  line `Uttar Pradesh (Alteration of Boundaries) Act, 1979 (31 of 1979), but excluding the territories`
  line `specified in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 4 of that Act.".`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (39391)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Construction of delimitation orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39391&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, any reference in any order`
  line `relating to delimitation of parliamentary constituencies, assembly constituencies or council`
  line constituencies—
  line
  line `(a) (i) to the State of Haryana, shall be construed as including the territories transferred to that`
  line `State from the State of Uttar Pradesh under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 4, but excluding`
  line `the territories transferred from the State of Haryana to the State of Uttar Pradesh under clause (b) of`
  line `that sub-section;`
  line
  line `(ii) to any district, sub-division, police-station or other administrative unit in the State of Haryana,`
  line `shall be construed as including that part of the territories, if any, transferred to that State, which is`
  line `included in that district, sub-division, police station or other administrative unit by order made under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) (i) to the State of Uttar Pradesh, shall be construed as including the territories transferred to`
  line `that State from the State of Haryana under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 4, but excluding the`
  line `territories transferred from the State of Uttar Pradesh to the State of Haryana under clause (a) of that`
  line sub-section;
  line
  line `(ii) to any district, sub-division, police-station or other administrative unit in the State of Uttar`
  line `Pradesh, shall be construed as including that part of the territories, if any, transferred to that State,`
  line `which is included in that district, sub-division, police-station or other administrative unit by order`
  line `made under sub-section (2) of section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (39392)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Provision as to sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39392&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every sitting member of the House of the People`
  line `representing any parliamentary constituency the extent of which has been altered by virtue of the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall, notwithstanding such alteration, be deemed, as from the appointed day, to`
  line `have been elected to that House by that constituency as so altered.`
  line
  line `(2) Every sitting member of the Legislative Assembly of the State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh`
  line `representing any assembly constituency the extent of which has been altered by virtue of the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall, notwithstanding such alteration, be deemed, as from the appointed day, to have been`
  line `elected to the said Legislative Assembly by that constituency as so altered.`
  line
  line `(3) Every sitting member of the Legislative Council of the State of Uttar Pradesh representing any`
  line `council constituency the extent of which has been altered by virtue of the provisions of this Act shall,`
  line `notwithstanding such alteration, be deemed, as from the appointed day, to have been elected to the said`
  line `Legislative Council by that constituency as so altered.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (39393)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Extension of jurisdiction of, and transfer of proceedings to, High Court of Punjab and Haryana.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39393&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as hereinafter provided—`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the High Court of Punjab and Haryana shall, as from the appointed day,`
  line `extend to the territories transferred by this Act from the State of Uttar Pradesh to the State of`
  line `Haryana; and`
  line
  line `(b) the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad shall, as from that day, have no jurisdiction in`
  line `respect of the said territories.`
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings pending in the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad immediately before the`
  line `appointed day as are certified by the Chief Justice of that High Court, having regard to the place of`
  line `accrual of the cause of action and other circumstances, to be proceedings which ought to be heard and`
  line `decided by the High Court of Punjab and Haryana shall, as soon as may be after such certification, be`
  line `transferred to the High Court of Punjab and Haryana.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), but save as hereinafter provided,`
  line `the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad shall have, and the High Court of Punjab and Haryana shall not`
  line `have, jurisdiction to entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme`
  line `Court, applications for review and other proceedings, where any such proceedings seek any relief in`
  line `respect of any order passed by the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad before the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, after such proceedings have been entertained by the High Court of Judicature at`
  line `Allahabad, it appears to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the High`
  line `Court of Punjab and Haryana, he shall order that they shall be so transferred and such proceedings shall`
  line `thereupon be transferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad—`
  line
  line `(a) before the appointed day in any proceedings transferred to the High Court of Punjab and`
  line `Haryana by virtue of sub-section (2), or`
  line
  line `(b) in any proceedings with respect to which the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad retains`
  line `jurisdiction by virtue of sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall, for all purposes, have effect not only as an order of the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad, but`
  line `also as an order made by the High Court of Punjab and Haryana.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to any rule made or direction given by the High Court of Punjab and Haryana, any such`
  line `person who immediately before the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of`
  line `Judicature at Allahabad as may be specified in this behalf by the Chief Justice of the High Court of`
  line `Punjab and Haryana having regard to the transfer of territories from the State of Uttar Pradesh to the State`
  line `of Haryana, shall be recognised as an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of Punjab and`
  line Haryana.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (39394)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Extension of jurisdiction of, and transfer of proceedings to, High Court at Allahabad.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39394&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as hereinafter provided`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad shall, as from the appointed day,`
  line `extend to the territories transferred by this Act from the State of Haryana to the State of Uttar`
  line `Pradesh; and`
  line
  line `(b) the High Court of Punjab and Haryana shall, as from that day, have no jurisdiction in respect`
  line `of the said territories.`
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings pending in the High Court of Punjab and Haryana immediately before the`
  line `appointed day as are certified by the Chief Justice of that High Court, having regard to the place of`
  line `accrual of the cause of action and other circumstances, to be proceedings which ought to be heard and`
  line `decided by the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad shall, as soon as may be after such certification, be`
  line `transferred to the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), but save as hereinafter provided,`
  line `the High Court of Punjab and Haryana shall have, and the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad shall not`
  line `have, jurisdiction to entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme`
  line `Court, applications for review and other proceedings, where any such proceedings seek any relief in`
  line `respect of any order passed by the High Court of Punjab and Haryana before the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, after such proceedings have been entertained by the High Court of Punjab and`
  line `Haryana, it appears to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the High`
  line `Court of Judicature at Allahabad, he shall order that they shall be so transferred and such proceedings`
  line `shall thereupon be transferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by the High Court of Punjab and Haryana`
  line
  line `(a) before the appointed day in any proceedings transferred to the High Court of Judicature at`
  line `Allahabad by virtue of sub-section (2); or`
  line
  line `(b) in any proceedings with respect to which the High Court of Punjab and Haryana retains`
  line `jurisdiction by virtue of sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall, for all purposes, have effect not only as an order of the High Court of Punjab and Haryana, but also`
  line `as an order made by the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to any rule made or direction given by the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad, any`
  line `such person who immediately before the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practise in the High`
  line `Court of Punjab and Haryana as may be specified in this behalf by the Chief Justice of the High Court of`
  line `Judicature at Allahabad having regard to the transfer of territories from the State of Haryana to the State`
  line `of Uttar Pradesh shall be recognised as an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of Judicature at`
  line Allahabad.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (39395)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Right to appear in any proceedings transferred under section 8 or section 9.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39395&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `who immediately before the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of Punjab`
  line `and Haryana or the High Court of Judicature at Allahabad and was authorised to appear in any`
  line `proceedings transferred under section 8 or section 9 shall have the right to appear in the High Court to`
  line `which the proceedings have been transferred in relation to those proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (39396)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39396&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of sections 8 and 9,—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in the High Court of Punjab and Haryana or the`
  line `High Court of Judicature at Allahabad until that Court has disposed of all issues between the parties,`
  line `including any issue with respect to the taxation of the costs of the proceedings and shall include`
  line `appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for review, petitions for`
  line `revision and petitions for writs;`
  line
  line `(b) references to the High Court of Punjab and Haryana or the High Court of Judicature at`
  line `Allahabad shall be construed as including references to a Judge or division court thereof, and`
  line `references to an order made by a court or a Judge shall be construed as including references to a`
  line `sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (39422)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Appropriation of moneys for expenditure in transferred territories under existing appropriation Acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39422&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day, any Act passed by the Legislature of the State of`
  line `Haryana or Uttar Pradesh before that day for the appropriation of any moneys out of the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of the State to meet any expenditure in respect of any part of the financial year in which the`
  line `appointed day falls shall have effect also in relation to the territories transferred to that State by the`
  line `provisions of Part II and it shall be lawful for the State Government to spend any amount on any service`
  line `in those territories out of the amount authorised by such Act to be expended for that service during the`
  line `financial year in that State.`
  line
  line `(2) The Governor of Haryana or of Uttar Pradesh may, after the appointed day, authorise such`
  line `expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the State as he deems necessary for any purpose or service in`
  line `the territories transferred to that State for a period of not more than six months beginning with the`
  line `appointed day pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislature of the State:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such authorisation shall be made so as to have effect for any period after the end of`
  line `the financial year in which the appointed day falls.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (39398)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Reports relating to accounts of Haryana and Uttar Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39398&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The reports of the Comptroller`
  line `and Auditor-General of India referred to in clause (2) of article 151 of the Constitution relating to the`
  line `accounts of the State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh in respect of any financial year ending before the`
  line `appointed day shall be submitted to the Governor of each of the States of Haryana and Uttar Pradesh who`
  line `shall cause them to be laid before the Legislature of the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (39399)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Land and goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39399&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Part, all land and all stores, articles`
  line `and other goods belonging to the State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh in the transferred territories shall, as`
  line `from the appointed day, pass to the State to which the territories are transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) In this section, the expression "land" includes immovable property of every kind and any rights in`
  line `or over such property.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (39400)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Arrears of taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39400&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The right of the State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh to recover arrears of any`
  line `tax or duty on property situate in the transferred territories, including land revenue, or to recover arrears`
  line `of any other tax or duty in any case where the place of assessment of that tax or duty is in the transferred`
  line `territories shall belong to the State to which the territories are transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (39401)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Right to recover loans and advances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39401&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The right to recover any loans or advances made before`
  line `the appointed day by the State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh to any local body, society, agriculturist, or`
  line `other person in the transferred territories shall belong to the State to which the territories are transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (39402)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Refund of taxes collected in excess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39402&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The liability of the State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh to`
  line `refund any tax or duty on property situate in the transferred territories including land revenue, collected in`
  line `excess shall be the liability of the State to which the territories are transferred, and the liability of the`
  line `State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh to refund any other tax or duty collected in excess in any case where`
  line `the place of assessment of the tax or duty is in the transferred territories shall also be the liability of the`
  line `State to which the territories are transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (39403)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Deposits.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39403&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The liability of the State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh in respect of any civil deposit or`
  line `local fund deposit made in the transferred territories shall, as from the appointed day, be the liability of`
  line `the State to which the territories are transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (39404)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Contracts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39404&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, before the appointed day, the State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh has`
  line `made any contract in the exercise of its executive power for any purposes of the State, that contract shall`
  line `be deemed to have been made in the exercise of the executive power—`
  line
  line `(a) if such purposes are, as from that day, purposes relatable exclusively to the transferred`
  line `territories, of the State to which the territories are transferred; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, of the State which made the contract, and all rights and liabilities which`
  line `have accrued, or may accrue, under any such contract shall, to the extent to which they are rights or`
  line `liabilities of the State which made the contract, be the rights or liabilities of the State specified in`
  line `clause (a) or clause (b) above.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, there shall be deemed to be included in the liabilities which have`
  line `accrued or may accrue under any contract—`
  line
  line `(a) any liability to satisfy an order or award made by any court or other tribunal in proceedings`
  line `relating to the contract; and`
  line
  line `(b) any liability in respect of expenses incurred in or in connection with any such proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) This section shall have effect subject to the other provisions of this Part relating to the`
  line `apportionment of liabilities in respect of loans, guarantees and other financial obligations.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (39405)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Liability in respect of actionable wrong.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39405&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the`
  line `State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh is subject to any liability in respect of an actionable wrong, other than`
  line `breach of contract, that liability shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the cause of action arose wholly within the transferred territories, be a liability of the State`
  line `to which the territories are transferred; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, continue to be a liability of the State which, immediately before that day,`
  line `was subject to such liability.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (39406)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Liability as guarantor of co-operative societies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39406&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed`
  line `day, the State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh is liable as guarantor in respect of any liability of a registered`
  line `co-operative society, that liability shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the area of the society's operations is limited to the transferred territories, be a liability of`
  line `the State to which the territories are transferred; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, continue to be a liability of the State which, immediately before that day,`
  line `was subject to such liability.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (39407)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Items in suspense.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39407&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `If any item in suspense is ultimately found to affect an asset or liability of`
  line `the nature referred to in any of the foregoing provisions of this Part, it shall be dealt with in accordance`
  line `with that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (39408)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Apportionment of assets or liabilities by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39408&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Where the States of Haryana and Uttar`
  line `Pradesh agree that the benefit or burden of any particular asset or liability should be apportioned between`
  line `them in a manner other than that provided for in the foregoing provisions of this Part, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained therein, the benefit or burden of that asset or liability shall be`
  line `apportioned in the manner agreed upon.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (39409)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power of Central Government to order allocation or adjustment in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39409&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line Where,
  line `by virtue of any of the provisions of this Part, either of the States of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh becomes`
  line `entitled to any property or obtains any benefits or becomes subject to any liability, and the Central`
  line `Government, on a reference made within a period of three years from the appointed day by either of the`
  line `States, is of opinion that it is just and equitable that that property or those benefits should be transferred`
  line `to, or shared with, the other State or that a contribution towards that liability should be made by the other`
  line `State, the said property or benefits shall be allocated in such manner between the two States, or the other`
  line `State shall make to the State subject to the liability such contribution in respect thereof, as the Central`
  line `Government may, after consultation with the two State Governments, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (39410)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Expenditure to be charged on the Consolidated Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39410&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `All sums payable by either the State`
  line `of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh to the other State by virtue of the provisions of this Part shall be charged on`
  line `the Consolidated Fund of the State by which such sums are payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (39411)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `State Financial Corporations and State Electricity Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39411&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) the Financial Corporations constituted under the State Financial Corporations`
  line `Act, 1951 (63 of 1951), for the States of Haryana and Uttar Pradesh; and`
  line
  line `(b) the State Electricity Boards constituted under the Electricity (Supply) Act, 1948 (54 of 1948),`
  line `for the said States,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to have been constituted for those States with their areas as altered by the provisions of`
  line `section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (39412)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Territorial extent of laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39412&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 4 shall not be deemed to have effected any`
  line `change in the territories to which any law in force immediately before the appointed day extends or`
  line `applies, and territorial references in any such law to the State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh shall, until`
  line `otherwise provided by a competent Legislature or other competent authority, be construed as meaning the`
  line `territories within that State immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (39413)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to adapt laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39413&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of facilitating the application of any law in relation to the`
  line `State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh, the appropriate Government may, before the expiration of two years`
  line `from the appointed day, by order, make such adaptations and modifications of the law, whether by way of`
  line `repeal or amendment as may be necessary or expedient, and thereupon every such law shall have effect`
  line `subject to the adaptations or modifications so made until altered, repealed or amended by a competent`
  line `Legislature or other competent authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression “appropriate Government” means as respects any law`
  line `relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List, the Central Government, and as respects any other law,`
  line `the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (39414)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39414&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has been`
  line `made for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal or authority, required`
  line `or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating its application in relation to the`
  line `State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh, construe the law in such manner, without affecting the substance, as`
  line `may be necessary or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (39415)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39415&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the State of Haryana or`
  line `Uttar Pradesh is a party to any legal proceedings with respect to any property, rights or liabilities`
  line `transferred to the other State under this Act, the other State shall be deemed to be substituted for the State`
  line `from which such property, rights or liabilities are transferred as a party to those proceedings, or added as`
  line `a party thereto, as the case may be, and the proceedings may continue accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (39416)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39416&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending immediately before the`
  line `appointed day before a court (other than a High Court), tribunal, authority or officer in any area which on`
  line `that day falls within the State of Haryana or Uttar Pradesh shall, if it is a proceeding/relatable exclusively`
  line `to any part of the territories which as from that day are the territories of the other State, stand transferred`
  line `to the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer in the other State.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding should stand transferred under sub-section (1),`
  line `it shall be referred to the High Court having jurisdiction in respect of the area in which the court, tribunal,`
  line `authority or officer before which, or before whom, such proceeding is pending on the appointed day, is`
  line `functioning, and the decision of that High Court shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) "proceeding" includes any suit, case or appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) "corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer" in a State means—`
  line
  line `(i) the court, tribunal, authority or officer in which, or before whom, the proceeding would`
  line `have lain if the proceeding had been instituted after the appointed day, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority or officer in that State as may be`
  line `determined after the appointed day by the Government of that State, or before the appointed day`
  line `by the Government of the other State, to be the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (39417)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Construction of boundary pillars, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39417&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be lawful for the State Government which is`
  line `responsible for the construction of any boundary pillar under sub-section (3) of section 3 to cause such`
  line `pillar to be constructed and maintained and no suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against`
  line `the State Government or any of its officers for anything in good faith done or intended to be done under`
  line `this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The boundary pillars shall be inspected jointly by the officers of the State Governments of`
  line `Haryana and Uttar Pradesh in accordance with such rules as the Central Government may make in this`
  line behalf.
  line
  line `(3) Whoever wilfully removes or injures any boundary pillars shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `of either description for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), an`
  line `offence under sub-section (3) may be inquired into and tried by a court in either of the States of Haryana`
  line `and Uttar Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (39418)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Validity of demarcation done before commencement of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39418&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `All things done and all steps`
  line `taken before the commencement of this Act in connection with the demarcation of the fixed boundaries`
  line `shall, in so far as they are in conformity with the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 3, be`
  line `deemed to have been done in accordance with law.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (39419)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Effect of provisions inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39419&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding any law, custom or usage which is inconsistent therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (39420)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39420&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the President may, by notified order, do anything, not inconsistent with such provisions which`
  line `appears to him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (39421)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290&sectionId=39421&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00047_197931_1517807325290
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
